Carbon Dioxide Removal is an opportunity to address one of the most pressing challenges of our time: climate change. By removing CO2 from the atmosphere, we can significantly reduce the impacts of global warming, such as rising temperatures, sea-level rise, and extreme weather events. Additionally, Carbon Dioxide Removal offers a pathway to achieve net-zero emissions, a crucial goal in mitigating climate change and transitioning to a sustainable future. This technology also opens up possibilities for innovative solutions and collaborations across sectors, driving the development of new industries and creating economic opportunities. Overall, Carbon Dioxide Removal presents a transformative opportunity to protect our planet and ensure a livable environment for future generations.

Carbon Dioxide Removal (CDR) techniques offer a path to mitigate the excess greenhouse gases that are not easily reduced through energy efficiency or renewable energy transitions alone. By actively removing CO2 from the atmosphere, these technologies and natural solutions can help achieve the global targets set under the Paris Agreement, striving to limit global warming to well below 2 degrees Celsius. CDR is particularly crucial for neutralizing emissions from hard-to-abate sectors and can potentially reverse some impacts of climate change, restoring ecosystems and enhancing biodiversity.
